Email harvesting is the process of collecting email addresses related to a target (person, company, or domain) using public sources.

👉 It’s widely used in:

Passive reconnaissance
Bug bounty
Penetration testing (authorized only)
Threat intelligence
-----------------------------------------

🔍 What Can You Find?
Employee emails (e.g., john@company.com)
Admin/support emails
Leaked emails from breaches
Email patterns (like firstname.lastname@domain.com)

👉 These become entry points for:

Phishing simulations
Credential testing (authorized)
Attack surface mapping

--------------------------------------------

Email Harvesting Tools
🔹1. theHarvester -> theHarvester -d example.com -b all
🔹2. Hunter.io -> Finds emails by domain
🔹3. EmailHippo -> Validates if an email exists
🔹4. Holehe -> Checks where an email is registered, Finds linked accounts (social media, services)
🔹5. Maltego -> maps: emails, domain, people
🔹6. Recon-ng -> Automates email discovery work with api
🔹7. SpiderFoot -> Fully automated scanning

